metadata.name: Echo #38
metadata.description:
"Echo" is a generative abstract artwork made with p5js and custom shaders

Based on my previous experience, known patterns and existing style preferences
Artwork is 100% code, no images used.

CONTROLS
KEYS:

- 1-3: Set resolution from 1x to 3x of the current dimension (possibly slower performance in higher values)
- S: Save a png file with the current resolution

----
ABOUT THE ARTIST
Want to know more ? please read the "SHORT BIO" section here in "Emotions" collection: https://www.fxhash.xyz/generative/22243

© May 2023  @Uniray_net | uniray.net

metadata.name: Helix #34
metadata.description:
"Helix" is a 100% code generative real time 3D sculpture. An interactive study to lighting and color. Move your mouse to set the light's position. Press the "V" key to view the object from different angles (rotation)

CONTROLS

KEYS:
- V: Render a different view (object view angle) on each key press
- B: Toggle Backlight (on/off)
- S: Save a png file
- R: Reset/reload
- SPACEBAR: Toggle light's position auto-update and also toggle (enable/disable) mouse move interactivity

MOUSE:
- Move: Moves (set) the light's position
- Click: Toggle light's position auto-update and mouse move interactivity (the same as the SPACEBAR)

----
Made with p5js (use WebGL canvas)

© May 2023  @Uniray_net | uniray.net

metadata.name: Cables and Clouds #89
metadata.description:
Capturing clouds... an old dream of mad scientist... coming true...
But wait... are they real clouds ? Maybe... maybe not...
Is it the real life ?
Is this just fantasy ?

Interaction.
Press h in live mode to list the possibilities.
Key 's'  : Save an image of the output at the current resolution
Key 1-9 : Change resolution
Key 'c' to change color palette
Key 'd' to toggle a special color mode to highlight the different components (and have the number of points used in your specific drawing).

Features.
18 different features displayed (format, color palettes, main elements characteristics, rare elements...).

metadata.name: Emotional Shell #180
metadata.description:
Manual Dutch Auction (DA): 72 · 54 · 40 · 30 · 24 · 20 every 8 minutes.
Auction will stop changing price when non-reserves are fully minted, and then drop one price tier.

---------

The feeling of being human – with all of its intricate hopes, struggles, and fleeting emotions – seems so unique that we assume artificial intelligence could never replicate our experience. And while we devise systems for solving unfathomably complex problems, generating algorithmic creativity, and unlocking regenerative biological possibilities, we simultaneously cling to the power and originality of emotional feeling – believing it to be the irreplaceable source of what makes us human.

If the body is our shell for emotion and soul, can an artificial humanoid be another vessel for these thoughts and feelings – for human essence itself? If our ‘soul’ is the last stand between us and the machines, what happens when the soul becomes transferable? That we may see answers to these questions looks more real every year, and is perhaps a little frightening. 

Emotional Shell uses introspective portraits of future selves to question what it means to be human, when the people around us are no longer human.

---------

Warning: This piece is GPU intensive, it may not render on lower end devices.

Press 1-3 to select from low, medium, and high quality settings
Press 'S' to save the image at the current scale
Press 'H' to save the image at 2400px resolution

Created with Three.js
For third party license information, please see bundle.js.LICENSE.txt

---------

TENDER x wwatkns
August 2022

metadata.name: Gen DOS Punk #270
metadata.description:
Gen DOS Punks - A Generative Tribute to DOS Punks!

Each Punk is a unique 1/1.

222 fxrand() functions in total to ensure almost no duplicates whatsoever!

Features weren't included due to a technical limitation. However if you want to see those, you can check the console logs - they're all there!

You can also triple-tap on a phone or click S on your keyboard to perform a "right-click save as".

-----

Find me on Twitter @uoisnlli

And find the 'DOS Punks' creator on Twitter @maxcapacity

#DOSLIFE

Not affiliated with DOS Punks or CryptoPunks/Larva Labs

metadata.name: Lusona #30
metadata.description:
A lusona is a drawing in the sand, created by a storyteller as they draw and narrate together. Sona are part of the tradition of the Chokwe people from south west Africa.
We became interested in these drawings when exploring culturally rich sources for mathematics teaching and we are delighted that we have been able to create this work inspired by them.

Keystrokes 1,2,3,4 & 7 will render the artwork at increasing resolutions.

metadata.name: Luminaries #4
metadata.description:
There is no light without dark.

Luminaries is a study in symmetry, contrast and flow, with a palette inspired by the twelve full moon names. Owning a Luminary enables you to request a signed print for an additional fee. 

You can learn more about features and prints at: https://www.phaust.art/luminary

Each Luminary is composed of moons in various phases. Their layout derived from a handful of geometries. They contrast with their surroundings: filled with glittering stars, inky strokes or solid colour. 

Backgrounds can split along lines of symmetry – with dark and light contrasting as strokes seamlessly flow across the two halves. 

Luminaries are alive. They’re in retrograde once a month, a day in which you’ll see yours in a new light.

------

Collection Size: 158. One for each of the confirmed moons in our solar system.

Palettes: 12 + 1. One for each of the full moons plus a rarer secret palette: Wolf, Snow, Worm, Pink, Flower, Strawberry, Buck, Sturgeon, Harvest, Hunter, Beaver, Cold, ????.

Retrograde: day of the month that your Luminary will change for one day only.

S: to save at high resolution. 

Prints: request from https://www.phaust.art/luminary
